snippet.textDisplay: Our thanks and respects to Gaurav and all Indians who liked the  National anthem and its melody. You people really are true lovers of music who really do not care about trivial politics and the usual cacophony emanating from medi extremists on both sides of the border. No matter what happens politically one thing will remain there, and which will transcend all debates and arguments and that is, we share the same roots. I am a retired soldier but its my conviction that a day will come when we two nations would exist like the US and Canada, as envisioned by the two great leaders of the Sub Continent, Maha aatma Mohandas Karamchand Gandhi and the Quaide Azam.
